# Shell commands and target environments

## Shell commands (RTK)

Prefix agent terminal commands with **`rtk`** when available (`rtk uv run pytest`, `rtk git diff`, `rtk git status`). It compacts output; passthrough is safe if no filter exists.

Transparent rewrite via global hook is preferred: `rtk init --global --agent cursor` (see `docs/ai_assisted_development.md`). Project rules are the fallback on native Windows or when RTK is not installed.

## Target environment approval

**Always ask** before running any command that is not read-only.

**Safe without asking** (local only):

- `rtk uv run pytest`, `rtk uv run ruff`
- `uv sync`
- `rtk git diff`, `rtk git status`, `rtk git log`

**Requires approval**:

- Live API calls with real keys (`WeatherAPITask` hits OpenWeatherMap)
- `git push`, network `git pull`
- Any deploy or production-side command

**When blocked or awaiting approval**: show the exact command for copy-paste; do not run it.

Override RTK for one command: `RTK_DISABLED=1 uv run pytest …`
